Changelog

All notable changes to ScreenSafe will be documented in this section.


VERSION [0.1.0] 

Added

* Added the initial concept for ScreenSafe as an Android app focused on monitoring screen time.
* Added the initial outline describing the business problem of excessive screen time.
* Added the first plan for core features such as usage limits, warnings, summaries, and settings.

Changed

* Changed the project from a simple app idea into an organized outline with defined goals and functionality.

Fixed

* Fixed the project focus so the app remained centered on digital wellness and healthier device habits.

VERSION [1.0.0] 

Added

* Added the six main wireframed screens:

  * Welcome Screen
  * Dashboard or Home Screen
  * Set Limit Screen
  * Warning or Alert Screen
  * Daily or Weekly Summary Screen
  * Settings Screen
* Added local settings storage.
* Added reminder frequency selection.
* Added weekly summary tracking.
* Added theme selection in Settings.
* Added warning-flow logic for daily screen time limits.
* Added basic Android screen-time tracking through UsageStatsManager.

Changed

* Changed the original concept into a more complete wireframe-based design.
* Changed the dashboard to include progress display and quick actions such as Set Limit, View Report, and Take a Break.
* Changed the settings design to include notification controls, reminder settings, daily summary settings, theme selection, reset options, and save options.

Fixed

* Fixed the alignment between the original outline, wireframe, and code plan so they matched more clearly.

VERSION [1.1.0]

Added

* Added Room database support for daily screen-time history.
* Added WorkManager for scheduled break reminders and daily summary tasks.
* Added local notifications for screen-time limit warnings and summary alerts.
* Added a real Summary Details screen to replace the earlier View More placeholder.
* Added a custom Application class to initialize notification channels.
* Added notification permission support for newer Android versions.

Changed

* Changed the project from a starter prototype into a more complete final version.
* Changed usage-history storage from simple preference-based tracking to a structured Room database.
* Changed the project architecture to better separate UI, storage, notifications, background work, and settings logic.
* Changed the app flow so the summary path is fully functional instead of partially planned.

Improved

* Improved persistence by saving daily usage history as structured database records.
* Improved reminder functionality with scheduled background workers.
* Improved the summary experience with a dedicated details screen.
* Improved the overall app quality by replacing placeholder logic with working implementations.
* Improved the codebase so it better reflects a finished academic project while still matching the original wireframes.

Fixed

* Fixed the incomplete View More summary flow.
* Fixed missing notification behavior by implementing actual notification delivery.
* Fixed unfinished permission-helper logic by replacing it with usable support code.
* Fixed weak history storage by moving it to a more reliable database-backed approach.


